The Ukrainian side has agreed to meet Russians without pre-conditions. The head of the regional administration of Kharkiv, in north eastern Ukraine, says local forces have reasserted full control of the city, after having fought Russian, troops in the streets. Meanwhile, a peace and security expert says Western countries should be careful in their interventions in the Russia and Ukraine conflict, saying they could walk into a trap that Russian President Vladimir Putin has set for them. Hostilities between the two countries, quickly turned deadly, when Russia, invaded Ukraine in the early hours of Thursday, Ukraine President Zelensky says that his country was invaded at four in the morning. The invasion has left thousands displaced, some dead, and anti-war protests have been triggered around the globe. Professor Anthoni van Nieuwkerk, says Ukraine deserves to be independent... --BBC/SABC--